cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.PL, cs.SE 

This paper proposes a framework for reasoning about degrees of belief in uncertain dynamic worlds, which is fundamental to many applications such as robotics and planning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with probabilistic reasoning, which is a common topic in machine learning, leading to the second likely sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions robotics, which suggests the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a methodology that can be coupled with a variety of existing inference solutions, which suggests the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper deals with uncertainty in dynamic systems, which is a common topic in software engineering, leading to the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
